 {"id":"frankenredis-r9h9","title":"redis parity: RESET and QUIT should reject script context","description":"Vendored Redis marks RESET and QUIT as NOSCRIPT in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/commands/reset.json and quit.json, but the local handlers at crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:13933 and crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:8683 return success without any script_nesting_level guard. Add Redis-compatible NOSCRIPT rejection after arity validation and cover both commands from Lua.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T04:07:11.688421378Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T04:07:38.071634896Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
